Concordia Career

2024: Competed in the 60m, 100m, 200m, 4x100, 4x400m and the sprint medley relay … part of an All-NSIC Indoor 4x400m team which placed second to earn All-NSIC honors … broke the school record in the 200m with a time of 21.22 at the NSIC Outdoor Track & Field Championships (5/9-11) … placed second with a career-best 60m time of 6.94 at the St. Olaf Ole Opener (1/20) … took first place in the 100m at the St. Thomas Joe Sweeney Invitational (5/1) … was part of a first-place 4x400m team at the Mark Schuck Open & Multi (1/26-27) and at the St. Thomas Opener (1/12) … took part in the first-place 4x100m team at the Hamline Invitational with a time of 41.16 (4/6) … placed eighth in the 100m at the NSIC Outdoor Championships (5/9-11) … tallied 19 top-five finishes in his various events on the season.

2023: Competed in the 60m, 200m, and 4x400m relay … career-best time of 6.99 at Chuck Petersen Open … placed fourth with a time of 23.14 in only 200m race of season at Chuck Petersen Open … was a part of first place 4x400m relay team at St. Thomas Indoor Invitational with a time of 3:24.96.

2022: Competed in the 60m, 100m, 200m, 400m, 4x100 relay, 4x200 relay, 4x400 relay, distance medley relay, and long jump ... finished second place in the 4x400 relay at the Chuck Peterson Open with a time of 3:46.18 ... set a season best in the long jump at the Mark Schuck Open and Multi with 5.36m (17' 7") ... set a personal best in the 60m with a time of 6.99 at the NSIC Indoor Track & Field Championships ... set a season best in the 4x100 relay at the Minnesota State Open with a time of 41:87 ... set a personal best in the 100m with a time of 10.73 at the Holst Invitational ... set a personal best at the Meet of the UnSaintly in the 400m with a time of 49.76 ... set a personal best in the 200m at the 2022 NSIC Outdoor Track & Field Championship with a time of 21.66.

2021: Competed in the 60m, 200m, 400m, 4x100m relay, 4x400m relays, long jump, and high jump during his freshman campaign ... established a new personal record in the high jump at the Chuck Peterson Dual with a mark of 1.75m ... set a new personal record in the long jump at the Washburn Open with a distance of 6.74m ... set new personal records and took first place in both the 60m and 200m at the Bison Open ... set a new personal record in the 400m at the NSIC Outdoor Challenge with a time of 53.06 seconds ... won two events and collected nine top-five finishes throughout the season.

Jordan High School: Lettered in football, basketball, and track and field all four years for the Hubmen … has received All-State honors three times, was named MVP of the Minnesota River Conference for track and field during his junior year, received All-Conference honors six times in his high school career, was named captain for his basketball and track and field teams … Helped lead his team to four Conference Championship titles and was part of the 2019 Class A State Championship team … Recorded a 22’4.75 jump in the long jump his senior year, recorded a 42’7.75 jump in the triple jump, part of a team that ran a 42.74 in the 4x100 and was part of a team that ran a 1:29.25 in the 4x200.

Personal: Plans to major in Graphic Design at CSP and wants to work with professional/college teams’ social media platforms in the future … Has three older sisters, one of them played basketball at South Dakota State University and one of them played volleyball at Luther College.
